servings: 2
---

Boil a full #kettle{}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Drain the @king prawns{225%g}.

Once hot, fry the prawns, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw prawns.

Meanwhile, pour the boiled water into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} on high heat.

Boil the @spaghetti{180%g}, ~{8%minutes}.

Once the prawns are cooked, stir in the @tomato puree{30%g}, @creme fraiche{75%g}, @harissa paste{50%g} (add less if you'd prefer things milder), @red wine stock paste{28%g}, @sugar{1%tsp} and @water{125%ml} (see pantry for both).

Bring to the boil then simmer, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add the @baby spinach{100%g} in handfuls, making sure it's piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir through the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g}.

> IMPORTANT: Cook so the prawns are opaque in the middle.

Once the pasta is cooked, drain and add to the sauce. Toss to coat.

Share the pasta between your #bowls{}.

Enjoy!